blic%20domain.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThey%20(INDIA%20parties)%20need%20to%20have%20a%20cohesive%20policy%2C%20a%20cohesive%20ideological%20framework%20and%20a%20cohesive%20programme%20for%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20talking%20about%20the%20state%20level%20or%20the%20national%20level%2C%20there%20has%20to%20be%20cohesiveness%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20thinks%20on%20issues%20that%20are%20of%20great%20national%20importance%20and%20unless%20that%20mechanism%20is%20put%20in%20place%20and%20unless%20there%20are%20spokespersons%20of%20the%20bloc%20who%20represent%20the%20views%20of%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20this%20can%20move%20forward%20very%20effectively%2C%26quot%3B%20Sibal%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20whether%20there%20should%20be%20a%20formal%20political%20structure%20in%20place%20for%20the%20bloc%2C%20Sibal%20said%20he%20has%20been%20batting%20for%20it%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20either%20it%20is%20not%20something%20that%20is%20palatable%20to%20somebody%20or%20the%20other%2C%20or%20they%20feel%20this%20is%20not%20the%20appropriate%20time%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20possibly%20talk%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20bloc%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%2C%20however%2C%20exuded%20confidence%20about%20the%20opposition's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20see%20a%20future%20for%20the%20opposition%2C%20what%20form%20it%20takes%2C%20what%20structure%20it%20takes%2C%20we'll%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Congress%20leader%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20National%20Developmental%20Inclusive%20Alliance%20(INDIA)%20of%20opposition%20parties%20came%20together%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20to%20counter%20the%20BJP-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20at%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EINDIA%20bloc%20constituents%2C%20particularly%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20AAP%2C%20were%20involved%20in%20sharp%20exchanges%20and%20traded%20barbs%20especially%20in%20the%20Delhi%20Assembly%20polls.%20Several%20political%20commentators%20cited%20lack%20of%20cohesiveness%20in%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20for%20the%20BJP%20gaining%20ground%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20and%20winning%20the%20elections%20in%20Haryana%2C%20Maharashtra%20and%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20Waqf%20(Amendment)%20Bill%20that%20could%20be%20tabled%20during%20the%20ongoing%20Budget%20session%20and%20the%20options%20for%20the%20opposition%2C%20Sibal%20said%20one%20must%20see%20what%20the%20NDA%20coalition%20partners%20are%20willing%20to%20do%20in%20this%20matter%20because%20the%20BJP%20does%20not%20have%20a%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet%20us%20see%20what%20their%20position%20is.%20There%20are%20elections%20coming%20in%20Bihar.%20I%20think%20that%20if%20they%20introduce%20the%20bill%2C%20they%20may%20be%20worried%20what%20impact%20that%20might%20have%20in%20the%20election%20process%20in%20Bihar%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20fallout%20of%20that%20is%20going%20to%20be.%20So%20let%20us%20wait%20and%20see.%20Of%20course%20if%20the%20bill%20is%20passed%20there%20are%20options%20available%20to%20those%20who%20wish%20to%20challenge%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Sibal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contentious%20delimitation%20issue%2C%20Sibal%20said%20it%20has%20very%20serious%20implications%20for%20the%20polity%20of%20the%20country%20and%20that%20is%20why%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Chief%20Minister%20MK%20Stalin%20called%20a%20meeting%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20representatives%2C%20including%20those%20of%20the%20Congress%20participated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20future%20of%20our%20polity%20but%20in%20any%20case%20the%20condition%20is%20that%20unless%20a%20new%20census%20is%20done%20the%20delimitation%20will%20not%20take%20place.We%20have%20not%20done%20a%20new%20census%20as%20in%202021%20also%20it%20was%20not%20done.%20First%20the%20census%20and%20then%20the%20delimitation.%20So%2C%20'abhi%20Dilli%20door%20ast'%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20senior%20advocate%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%2C%20who%20was%20a%20Union%20minister%20during%20the%20UPA%201%20and%20UPA%202%20governments%2C%20quit%20the%20Congress%20in%20May%202022%20and%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20as%20an%20Independent%20member%20with%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party's%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742727060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fbtep0u88_kapil-sibal_625x300_12_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-must-appear-to-be-a-bloc-not-unbloc-itself-kapil-sibal-7991281%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22INDIA%20should%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bbloc%20and%20not%20un-bloc%26quot%3B%20itself%20in%20the%20manner%20that%20it%20does%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Kapil%20Sibal%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon%2C%20Tesla%20%26amp%3B%20other%20US%20companies%20that%20bagged%20maximum%20H-1B%20visas%20in%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742726962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119375666%2Cimgsize-45278.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Famazon-tesla-and-x-other-us-companies-that-bagged-maximum-h-1b-visas-in-2024%2Farticleshow%2F119375683.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon%20and%20Tesla%20are%20among%20the%20top%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program%20in%202025%2C%20securing%20thousands%20of%20approvals.%20These%20companies%20rely%20on%20skilled%20foreign%20workers%20for%20roles%20in%20engineering%20and%20research.%20Amazon%20leads%20with%209%2C265%20approvals%2C%20followed%20by%20Cognizant%20and%20Google.%20Indian%20IT%20firms%20like%20Infosys%20and%20TCS%20also%20feature%20prominently%20among%20top%20H-1B%20visa%20recipients.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Famazon-tesla-and-x-other-us-companies-that-bagged-maximum-h-1b-visas-in-2024%2Farticleshow%2F119375683.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Military%20spouses%20relied%20on%20federal%20jobs.%20Then%20came%20DOGE.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228164%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20American%20flag%20in%20front%20of%20someone's%20face.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ddc8ed63d72727e197f840%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226123%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20military%20spouses%2C%20getting%20fired%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20poses%20unique%20familial%20and%20financial%20challenges.%3Cp%3EHossein%20Fatemi%20%2F%20Middle%20East%20Images%20%2F%20Middle%20East%20Images%20via%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBI%20spoke%20to%20federally%20employed%20military%20spouses%20about%20how%20mass%20firings%20have%20impacted%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20said%20the%20changes%2C%20which%20one%20called%20'psychological%20warfare%2C'%20have%20scrambled%20familial%20planning.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOf%20employed%20military%20spouses%2C%2027%25%20work%20for%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20compared%20to%202%25%20of%20Americans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Cassandra%20Ramsey%20first%20arrived%20at%20a%20US%20Army%20base%20in%20Wiesbaden%2C%20Germany%2C%20in%20October%2C%20she%20met%20with%20the%20employment%20readiness%20office.%20An%20employee%20said%20she'd%20get%20a%20federal%20government%20job%2C%20no%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Ramsey%2C%2027%2C%20did%20get%20a%20job.%20On%20February%2025%20she%20received%20an%20offer%20to%20work%20as%20a%20substitute%20teacher%20through%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20Education%20Activity.%20By%20March%206%2C%20four%20days%20before%20she%20was%20meant%20to%20step%20into%20the%20classroom%2C%20the%20job%20was%20put%20on%20hold%20because%20of%20efforts%20by%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's%20administration%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-agencies-musk-doge-targeted-list-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhite%20House%20DOGE%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20shrink%20the%20federal%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamsey%20is%20one%20of%20many%20federally%20employed%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20for%20some%2C%20formerly%20federally%20employed%20%E2%80%94%20military%20spouses%20who%20have%20been%20affected%20by%20DOGE's%20efforts%2C%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-doge-layoffs-probationary-employees-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirings%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20return-to-office%20mandates.%20BI%20spoke%20to%20four%20recently%20fired%20and%20current%20federally%20employed%20military%20spouses%20about%20how%20the%20changes%20are%20impacting%20military%20families%2C%20whose%20lives%20are%20often%20defined%20by%20frequent%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20typically%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20more%20stable%20work%20option%20for%20military%20spouses%2C%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eearly%20weeks%20of%20Trump's%20second%20term%20have%20upended%20that%20idea%20%E2%80%94%20for%20those%20BI%20spoke%20with%2C%20this%20time%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bdisheartening%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdisconcerting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20military%20spouses%20is%20more%20than%20five%20times%20than%20the%20national%20average%2C%20at%2021%25%2C%20according%20to%20a%20December%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fsites%2Fdolgov%2Ffiles%2FVETS%2Ffiles%2FMilitary-Spouses-Fact-Sheet-2024-12-13.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor.%20Of%20those%20employed%2C%20about%2027%25%20work%20for%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20compared%20to%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2025%2F01%2F07%2Fwhat-the-data-says-about-federal-workers%2F%23how-many-federal-workers-are-there%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%25%20of%20Americans%20overall%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20administration%20has%20made%20efforts%20to%20protect%20military%20families%20from%20some%20of%20the%20recent%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20like%20when%20the%20Office%20of%20Management%20and%20Budget%20put%20out%20a%20memo%20in%20February%20exempting%20military%20spouses%20on%20remote%20work%20agreements%20from%20a%20return%20to%20office%20mandate.%20The%20families%20BI%20spoke%20with%2C%20however%2C%20said%20the%20rollout%20has%20been%20shaky%2C%20leaving%20their%20lives%20in%20a%20state%20of%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22beb43f3e-84a0-400b-8029-feeae0ee2498%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFederal%20employment%20is%20typically%20attractive%20for%20military%20spouses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ramsey%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20an%20air%20traffic%20controller%2C%20moved%20to%20Germany%20for%20their%20first%20permanent%20change%20of%20station%2C%20she%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20find%20a%20job.%20However%2C%20federal%20employment%20seemed%20like%20a%20viable%20option%2C%20especially%20because%20the%20government%20gives%20military%20spouses%20certain%20preferences%20in%20the%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20encourage%20military%20spouses%20to%20work%20for%20the%20federal%20government%20because%20all%20their%20jobs%20are%20specifically%20transferable.%20They%20encourage%20them%20so%20much%20that%20they%20have%20people%20stationed%20at%20every%20friggin'%20base%20to%20help%20you%20write%20your%20friggin'%20resume%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramsey%20told%20BI%20in%20early%20March.%20She%20only%20applied%20for%20federal%20jobs%20when%20arriving%20in%20Germany%2C%20and%20though%20her%20job%20offer%20is%20still%20technically%20valid%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsome-federal-worker-job-offers-revoked-memo-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20hold%20indefinitely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222101%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ramsey%20and%20her%20husband%20in%20Germany%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ddcc4163d72727e197f963%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Cassandra%20Ramsey%20moved%20to%20Germany%2C%20she%20was%20told%20she'd%20be%20able%20to%20get%20a%20government%20job%20easily.%3Cp%3ECassandra%20Ramsey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEmmalee%20Gruesen%2C%2039%2C%20became%20a%20government%20contractor%20in%202008%20and%20a%20civil%20servant%20in%202015.%20She%20met%20her%20husband%20while%20they%20were%20both%20working%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20%E2%80%94%20he%20bummed%20a%20ride%20from%20her%20to%20work%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20used%20to%20moving%20often.%20Her%20family%20relocated%20three%20times%20in%20three%20years%20and%20has%20lived%20in%20Charlottesville%2C%20Virginia%2C%20for%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half.%20She's%20currently%20on%20a%20remote%20work%20agreement%20and%20the%20arrangement%20has%20allowed%20her%20to%20maintain%20a%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20talk%20about%20service.%20For%20me%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20service.%20It's%20a%20matter%20of%20convenience%2C%26quot%3B%20Gruesen%20told%20BI.%20She%20said%20she%20considered%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20last%20year%2C%20but%20didn't%20mainly%20because%20she%20wasn't%20sure%20it%20would%20work%20well%20with%20her%20husband's%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20government%20contractor%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%20who%20was%20fired%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%20said%20working%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20as%20a%20military%20spouse%20is%20challenging%20because%20you%20have%20to%20start%20over%20with%20every%20move.%20The%20contractor%2C%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20for%20fear%20of%20retaliation%2C%20said%20contracting%20gave%20her%20the%20flexibility%20and%20financial%20stability%20that%20suited%20her%20family's%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20out%20of%20a%20job%2C%20both%20she%20and%20Ramsey%20independently%20told%20BI%20that%20they're%20done%20working%20for%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20done.%20I'm%20tapped%20out.%20I%20don't%20give%20a%20sh%E2%80%94%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20benefits%20are%20not%20worth%20it%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225051c000-ca71-4180-99bc-f567080c73d5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanges%20that%20feel%20like%20'psychological%20warfare'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGruesen%20is%20still%20on%20a%20remote%20work%20agreement%2C%20as%20is%20allowed%20under%20OPM's%20memo%20exempting%20military%20spouses%20from%20returning%20to%20the%20office.%20Yet%20she%20said%20that%20a%20senior%20executive%20in%20the%20Navy%20told%20her%20in%20a%20meeting%20she%20might%20have%20to%20report%20to%20a%20Defense%20Department%20facility%20near%20her%2C%20though%20she%20hasn't%20heard%20that%20from%20other%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCommon%20sense%20has%20left%20the%20building%20in%20implementation%2C%26quot%3B%20Gruesen%20said%20of%20the%20OPM%20memos.%20A%20swing%20voter%20who%20has%20supported%20both%20parties%2C%20she%20blames%20agency%20leadership%20more%20than%20Trump%20for%20the%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20not%20all%20military%20spouses%20can%20benefit%20from%20the%20remote%20work%20exemption%20as%20outlined%20in%20February's%20memo%3A%20some%20employees%20on%20telework%20agreements%20have%20been%20called%20back%20to%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20including%20a%20DC-based%20DoD%20employee%20whose%20husband%20is%20in%20the%20Marines%20and%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20for%20fear%20of%20retaliation.%20BI%20has%20verified%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20only%20accepted%20her%20current%20job%20because%20it%20was%20eligible%20for%20telework%2C%20with%20two%20days%20a%20week%20in%20person.%20Now%2C%20she%20said%20she%20is%20being%20asked%20to%20be%20back%20in%20the%20office%20full%20time%20starting%20April%202%2C%20because%20OPM's%20memo%20applies%20to%20remote%20workers%2C%20not%20teleworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20asked%20if%20she%20could%20be%20converted%20to%20a%20remote%20employee%20and%20keep%20working%20three%20days%20from%20home.%20She%20wrote%20a%20letter%2C%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20asking%20for%20an%20exemption.%20So%20far%2C%20nothing%20has%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20able%20to%20work%20from%20home%20three%20days%20a%20week%20has%20saved%20us%20tremendously.%20It%20saved%20us%20money.%20It's%20saved%20us%20time.%20It's%20kind%20of%20allowed%20us%20still%20to%20have%20our%20marriage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20solid%2062%20miles%20away%20from%20her%20office%2C%20she%20spends%20between%20three%20and%20four%20hours%20commuting%20each%20day%2C%20leaving%20the%20house%20at%205%3A45%20am%20and%20coming%20home%20after%206%3A00%20pm.%20On%20those%20days%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20like%20I'm%20a%20robot%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Her%20husband%20has%20to%20leave%20his%20job%20at%20the%20marines%20early%20to%20pick%20up%20their%20daughter%20from%20daycare%2C%20and%20he'll%20have%20to%20do%20so%20every%20weekday%20come%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-signs-executive-order-limiting-federal-hiring-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20federal%20hiring%20freeze%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20can't%20apply%20for%20other%20jobs%20closer%20to%20her%20home.%20The%20series%20of%20changes%20has%20felt%20to%20her%20like%20%26quot%3Bpsychological%20warfare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20federal%20government%20has%20been%20kind%20of%20like%20stability%20in%20our%20life.%20It's%20been%20like%20the%20one%20stability.%20But%20right%20now%20it's%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204d0f9f1-6b58-43ab-9454-b3714b7c89ba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFamily%20and%20financial%20planning%20upended%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20OPM's%20memo%20protects%20some%20military%20spouses%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-reduction-in-force-plans-department-closures-doge-firings-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20doesn't%20spare%20them%20from%20the%20reductions%20in%20force%2C%20or%20RIFs%2C%20that%20are%20coming%20across%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DoD%20employee's%20husband%20is%20up%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20and%20if%20he%20gets%20it%20he'll%20be%20gone%20for%20six%20months.%20Assuming%20she%20still%20has%20a%20job%20at%20that%20point%20and%20can't%20keep%20teleworking%2C%20she%20said%20she%20will%20likely%20have%20to%20take%20leave%20without%20pay%20so%20that%20she%20doesn't%20have%20a%20gap%20in%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20started%20talking%20about%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20she%20gets%20fired%20%E2%80%94%20they'll%20probably%20leave%20Maryland%2C%20with%20its%20high%20prices%2C%20and%20move%20back%20home%20to%20the%20midwest.%20She%20said%20her%20husband%2C%20a%20marine%20with%2010%20years%20of%20service%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edoesn't%20know%20what%20to%20make%20of%20the%20federal%20government's%20recent%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20just%20feels%20like%2C%20you're%20not%20supporting%20me%20when%20I'm%20here%20to%20support%20America%20and%20American%20families.%20But%20no%20one%20is%20supporting%20my%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGruesen%20is%20also%20preparing%20for%20a%20RIF%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20her%20coworkers%20have%20more%20government%20experience%20than%20she%20does%2C%20despite%20her%20having%20been%20a%20civil%20servant%20for%2010%20years.%20If%20she's%20fired%2C%20she%20said%20she%20and%20her%20two%20sons%20will%20likely%20move%20into%20her%20mom's%201%2C691%20square-foot%20home%20in%20California.%20They'd%20move%20out%20of%20their%20%243%2C000%2Fmonth%20rental%20in%20Charlottesville%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20would%20move%20into%20a%20studio%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20stretching%20his%20single%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20is%20too%20old%20to%20provide%20childcare%2C%26quot%3B%20Gruesen%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20if%20it's%20a%20matter%20of%20paying%20for%20childcare%20in%20an%20area%20that's%20expensive%20or%20not%20having%20a%20job%2C%20well%20then%20I'm%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20exiting%20the%20workforce%20at%20least%20temporarily.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223462%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Emmalee%20Gruesen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ddcb5b63d72727e197f90b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225193%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmmalee%20Gruesen%20said%20her%20family%20might%20have%20to%20split%20up%20if%20she's%20fired%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense.%3Cp%3EEmmalee%20Gruesen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20contractor%20who%20worked%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs%20talked%20to%20BI%2C%20she%20was%20a%20week%20into%20the%20job%20hunt.%20With%20her%20husband%20planning%20to%20retire%20soon%20and%20paying%20for%20professional%20training%2C%20she%20was%20already%20starting%20to%20pull%20on%20her%20professional%20connections%20to%20try%20to%20find%20a%20job%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20constantly%20starting%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20military%20spouses.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20I%20am%20right%20now.%20I'm%20trying%20right%20now.%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20anything%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20moving%20forward%20at%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e9cc124-47c6-48b0-94d8-5aebd1d6a0ad%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitary%20recruitment%20and%20retention%20could%20be%20impacted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbluestarfam.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FBSF_2023_MFLS_Comp_Report_Executive_Summ.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20annual%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Blue%20Star%20Families%20found%20that%20military%20spouse%20employment%20ranked%20as%20the%20top%20issue%20for%20active-duty%20spouses%20and%20a%20top-five%20issue%20for%20active-duty%20service%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGruesen%20said%20that%20spousal%20employment%20has%20posed%20recruitment%20challenges%20for%20years%20and%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20recent%20actions%20have%20only%20made%20them%20worse.%20Without%20a%20two-income%20household%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20have%20a%20family%2C%20making%20recruitment%20less%20and%20less%20attractive%20to%20young%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20an%20all-volunteer%20force%2C%20somebody's%20not%20going%20to%20set%20aside%20having%20a%20family%20for%2020%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you're%20female%2C%20you%20can't%2C%20like%20you%20cannot%20serve%20from%2025%20to%2045%2C%20or%20even%2020%20to%2040%20and%20still%20have%20a%20family.%20It%20is%20biologically%20unlikely%20%E2%80%94%20not%20impossible%2C%20but%20it's%20unrealistic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DoD%20employee%20said%20she%20could%20see%20DOGE's%20recent%20efforts%20to%20slash%20the%20federal%20workforce%20impacting%20recruitment%2C%20mainly%20for%20those%20who%20are%20already%20married.%20But%20more%20than%20that%2C%20she%20sees%20it%20impacting%20re-enlistment%20numbers%20%E2%80%94%20her%20own%20husband%20has%20talked%20about%20leaving%20the%20Marines%20if%20things%20don't%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contractor%20also%20foresees%20challenges%20for%20retention%2C%20saying%20that%20there%20might%20be%20people%20who%20leave%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20the%20detrimental%20effect%20that%20it's%20having%20on%20military%20families.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Ramsey%20is%20still%20in%20Germany%2C%20living%20in%20military%20base%20housing%20and%20paying%20relatively%20few%20bills.%20She%20feels%20guilty%20sometimes%20for%20complaining%20about%20her%20situation%20because%20she%20knows%20other%20military%20families%20have%20it%20way%20worse.%20But%20if%20her%20husband%20is%20pulled%20out%20of%20Germany%20and%20there%20aren't%20any%20federal%20jobs%20for%20her%20back%20home%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe'd%20just%20be%20screwed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMadison%20Hoff%20contributed%20to%20reporting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-spouses-affected-doge-federal-job-cuts-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742726821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ddc8ed63d72727e197f840%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-spouses-affected-doge-federal-job-cuts-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Military%20spouses%20say%20they%20rely%20on%20the%20federal%20government%20for%20jobs.%20When%20mass%20firings%20