ations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20could%20give%20flashing%20through%20my%20mind%20like%20neon%20lights.%20They%20were%20giant%20ear%20plugs.%20They%20were%20for%20stopping%20bleeding%20noses.%20They%20were%20for%20cleaning%20between%20dirty%20bathroom%20tiles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20effort%20to%20explain%20a%20natural%20part%20of%20life%2C%20and%20something%20that%20I%20thought%20knowing%20about%20would%20benefit%20him.%20So%20I%20took%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20explained%20how%20a%20woman's%20body%20gets%20ready%20to%20have%20a%20baby%20every%20month%2C%20and%20when%20she%20doesn't%20have%20a%20baby%2C%20it%20doesn't%20need%20everything%20she's%20stored%20up%20for%20it%2C%20so%20it%20comes%20out%20as%20blood%2C%20and%20tampons%20are%20something%20a%20woman%20can%20use%20to%20help%20with%20that.%20I'm%20relieved%20I%20went%20down%20that%20path%2C%20as%20I%20think%20my%20son%20asked%20me%20fewer%20questions%20about%20it%20than%20if%20I%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-lies-people-tell-kids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emade%20something%20up%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20I%20would%20have%20just%20wound%20myself%20up%20in%20a%20web%20of%20lies%20that%20I'd%20only%20have%20to%20undo%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20gave%20me%20a%20flashback%20of%20how%20my%20heart%20sank%20when%2C%20as%20a%20young%20girl%2C%20I%20found%20out%20that%20I'd%20have%20to%20bleed%20every%20month.%20I%20didn't%20know%20it%20was%20part%20of%20the%20reproductive%20cycle%2C%20as%20my%20all-important%20life%20briefing%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-daughter-was-shocked-when-we-had-the-period-talk-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eperiods%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20didn't%20come%20from%20my%20own%20parents%2C%20but%20from%20one%20of%20my%20friends%20while%20we%20were%20playing%20during%20recess%20at%20school.%20My%20mom%20eventually%20found%20out%20that%20I%20knew%20about%20periods%2C%20so%20she%20called%20me%20in%20for%20a%20talk%20after%20dinner%20one%20night.%20She%20basically%20reiterated%20what%20my%20friend%20had%20already%20told%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4ff56b4-fe4c-4fbf-8a7a-63659ab28eb9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20parents%20didn't%20speak%20openly%20about%20many%20things%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20told%20things%20on%20a%20need-to-know%2C%20often%20too%20late%2C%20basis%20was%20how%20my%20parents%20operated.%20They%20grew%20up%20in%20conservative%2C%20Catholic%20families%20where%20parents%20were%20not%20to%20be%20questioned%2C%20and%20lines%20of%20communications%20were%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20open.%20I%20never%20even%20had%20a%20sex%20talk%20with%20my%20parents.%20Instead%2C%20at%20my%20Catholic%20high%20school%2C%20we%20had%20a%20visit%20from%20church%20representatives%20who%20advised%20a%20room%20full%20of%2016-year-olds%20that%20the%20best%20form%20of%20contraception%20was%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsex-ed-things-wrong-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esave%20yourself%20for%20marriage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20recall%20other%20occasions%20where%20my%20parents%20told%20me%20significant%20pieces%20of%20information%20to%20do%20with%20our%20family%20well%20after%20the%20fact%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20how%20it%20made%20me%20feel%20%E2%80%94%20that%20my%20feelings%20and%20voice%20didn't%20count%2C%20and%20that%20I%20wasn't%20important.%20As%20a%20parent%20myself%20now%2C%20I%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20grow%20up%20feeling%20that%20they%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiving-autistic-kids-autonomy-bedtime-clothes-routine-helps-them-thrive-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20a%20say%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20how%20(some)%20things%20happen%20in%20our%20house%2C%20and%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20respect%20and%20value%20them%20as%20intelligent%20humans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234841a2c-b49b-4aa0-aef2-77fc013e5e9e%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20don't%20hold%20back%20in%20my%20house%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20our%20beliefs%2C%20my%206-year-old%20is%20also%20aware%20of%20other%20seemingly%20grown-up%20topics%20like%20menopause%20and%20adoption.%20The%20conversation%20about%20menopause%20came%20about%20when%20he%20asked%20why%20his%20grandmother%20wouldn't%20be%20having%20any%20more%20children.%20I%20can't%20quite%20remember%20how%20we%20got%20talking%20about%20adoption%2C%20but%20it%20made%20sense%20for%20him%20to%20understand%20it%20as%20my%20cousin%20is%20adopted.%20War%20has%20come%20up%20too%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20current%20conflicts%20constantly%20being%20featured%20on%20the%20news%2C%20but%20admittedly%2C%20that%20has%20been%20a%20harder%20one%20to%20explain%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20something%20we%20proactively%20bring%20up.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20while%2C%20I%20felt%20proud%20of%20my%20abilities%20as%20a%20parent%20to%20talk%20about%20these%20tough%20topics%20with%20my%20son%2C%20laying%20the%20foundation%20for%20more%20open%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthree-questions-that-get-teenagers-to-talk-to-me-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eproductive%20conversations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20he%20gets%20older%2C%20and%20with%20his%20younger%20brother%2C%20too%2C%20although%20he's%20only%202.%20Then%20my%20father-in-law%2C%20his%20beloved%20Grandad%2C%20died%20unexpectedly%20this%20month.%20It%20took%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20a%20whole%20week%20to%20break%20the%20news%20to%20him.%20We%20were%20dreading%20the%20conversation%20and%20kept%20putting%20it%20off.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20our%20surprise%2C%20our%20son's%20response%20to%20the%20tragic%20news%20was%20calm%20and%20rational.%20He%20knew%20Grandad%20had%20been%20in%20hospital%2C%20but%20we%20were%20all%20expecting%20him%20to%20recover%20and%20return%20home.%20He%20asked%20a%20few%20questions%20about%20what%20happened%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20didn't%20seem%20too%20disturbed%20as%20he%20figured%20he'd%20see%20Grandad%20again%20in%20heaven%20anyway.%20I%20don't%20know%20whether%20to%20be%20relieved%20or%20concerned%20at%20his%20lack%20of%20distress%2C%20but%20I%20have%20to%20remember%2C%20he%20is%20only%206%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fhow-to-talk-to-kids-about-death%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeath%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20big%20concept%20to%20grasp.%20I'm%20open%20to%20continuing%20the%20conversation%20as%20he%20processes%20the%20loss%20to%20our%20family.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d9e3ea7-0e2d-4bc9-b235-58d303d14261%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe're%20open%2C%20but%20keep%20things%20age-appropriate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20cause%20anxiety%20by%20over-explaining%20concepts%20that%20require%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20maturity%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20my%20son%20has%20started%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20environment%20at%20school%2C%20so%20we%20talk%20about%20how%20important%20it%20is%20to%20look%20after%20our%20Earth%2C%20but%20we%20haven't%20gone%20into%20detail%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fclimate-change%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20also%20don't%20want%20to%20impose%20societal%20norms%20and%20views%20on%20him%20that%20only%20perpetuate%20negative%20associations.%20Race%20has%20come%20up%20in%20our%20conversations%2C%20but%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20noticing%20that%20someone%20has%20a%20different%20skin%20color%20and%20talking%20about%20why%20that%20is.%20My%20philosophy%20is%20that%20if%20he%20sees%20racial%20difference%20as%20normal%2C%20then%20he's%20less%20likely%20to%20adopt%20racist%20views.%20We%20also%20have%20different%20races%20in%20our%20family%20background%20so%20we%20make%20a%20point%20of%20talking%20about%20all%20the%20interesting%20and%20fun%20things%20about%20those%20cultures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20these%20conversations%20with%20my%20son%20has%20made%20me%20realize%20what%20a%20huge%20responsibility%20parents%20have%20to%20explain%20to%20our%20kids%20about%20how%20the%20world%20and%20life%20works.%20They%20look%20to%20us%20for%20reassurance%20about%20what's%20okay%2C%20and%20whether%20they'll%20be%20okay.%20But%20we%20also%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20not%20impart%20our%20own%20views%2C%20or%20accepted%20world%20views%2C%20on%20them%20too.%20By%20speaking%20to%20my%20son%20openly%20and%20honestly%20about%20these%20grown-up%20topics%2C%20I'm%20hoping%20to%20empower%20him%20to%20have%20the%20curiosity%20to%20seek%20the%20knowledge%20to%20come%20to%20his%20own%20conclusions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-avoid-hard-talks-with-kids-know-about-periods-death-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742724301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67db1e3969253ccddf99bc93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-avoid-hard-talks-with-kids-know-about-periods-death-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20parents%20avoided%20talks%20about%20hard%20topics.%20I'm%20doing%20things%20differently%2C%20answering%20my%206-yea