Blue%20Origin.%3Cp%3EInkhouse%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETechnologist%20Lane%20Bess%20reflects%20on%20his%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-new-glenn-blue-origin-launch-elon-musk-spacex-2025-1%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlue%20Origin%3C%2Fa%3E%20space%20trips.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBess%20said%20each%20trip%20renewed%20his%20sense%20of%20what%20matters%20in%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20called%20for%20more%20visionary%20investments%20in%20space%20technology%20and%20exploration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20conversation%20with%20tech%20industry%20veteran%20Lane%20Bess.%20He%20founded%20Bess%20Ventures%20and%20is%20CEO%20of%20Deep%20Instinct%2C%20a%20deep%20learning-powered%20cybersecurity%20company.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20chairman%20of%20Blaize%20AI%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%2C%20and%20the%20former%20COO%20of%20Zscaler.%20He%20does%20not%20have%20financial%20ties%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fblue-origin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBlue%20Origin%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20to%20space%20twice%20in%20about%20three%20years.%20Each%20time%2C%20I've%20returned%20with%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20what%20matters%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-origin-launches-6-passengers-to-the-edge-of-space-including-gmas-michael-strahan-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20first%20trip%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202021%20and%20my%20second%20this%20past%20February.%20Each%20flight%20was%20just%2010%20minutes%20long%2C%20but%20Earth%20looks%20completely%20different%20when%20you%20take%20off%20and%20when%20you%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20back%20this%20time%20with%20several%20questions%20about%20the%20state%20of%20our%20world.%20Since%20my%20first%20trip%2C%20war%20has%20escalated.%20I%20thought%20this%20then%20%E2%80%94%20and%20still%20do%20now%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20limitation%20to%20what%20humanity%20can%20achieve%20is%20our%20ability%20to%20get%20along%20with%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20see%20instead%20is%20a%20thirst%20for%20power%2C%20a%20change%20in%20how%20people%20see%20politics%2C%20and%20people%20compromising%20the%20founding%20ideas%20of%20our%20constitutional%20forefathers%20for%20things%20that%20just%20advantage%20one%20country%20over%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20and%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20shouldn't%20be%20the%20only%20three%20people%20on%20Earth%20who%20have%20a%20say%20in%20how%20the%20rest%20of%20humanity%20lives%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20might%20make%20you%20think%20we%20should%20find%20another%20place%20to%20go%20because%20we're%20going%20to%20mess%20this%20up.%20We%20won't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-plan-colonize-mars-dont-count-on-it-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolonize%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E%20anytime%20soon%2C%20but%20maybe%20it%20has%20to%20start%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0a02a60-8c2a-40d0-a3fb-77a1a4594240%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lifetime%20curiosity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20fascinated%20by%20rockets%20since%20I%20was%20a%20child.%20Even%20before%20I%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20I%20remember%20going%20to%20the%20local%20hobby%20store%20%E2%80%94%20where%20I'd%20have%20to%20lie%20about%20my%20age%20%E2%80%94%20to%20buy%20these%20model%20rocket%20engines%20(which%20were%20obviously%20flammable).%20It's%20a%20passion%20I%20grew%20to%20share%20with%20my%20son%2C%20Cameron%2C%20who%20also%20accompanied%20me%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-origin-astronaut-twitch-streamer-jeff-bezos-rocket-space-dream-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20first%20space%20trip%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20later%2C%20it%20became%20possible%20for%20civilians%20to%20go%20to%20space.%20Fortunately%2C%20by%20then%2C%20I%20had%20made%20great%20exits%20from%20my%20previous%20cybersecurity%20companies%2C%20Palo%20Alto%20Networks%20and%20Zscaler%2C%20so%20I%20could%20afford%20to%20bid%20on%20a%20Blue%20Origin%20seat%20in%20an%20auction.%20I%20had%20also%20been%20looking%20into%20investing%20in%20space%20technology%20through%20my%20family%20office%2C%20Bess%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20right%20before%20Thanksgiving%2C%20Blue%20Origin's%20operations%20and%20civilian%20sales%20director%20contacted%20me%20about%20joining%20its%20third%20flight.%20I%20was%20contacted%20again%20in%20January%20of%20this%20year%20when%20a%20seat%20opened%20on%20the%2010th%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20disclose%20exactly%20how%20much%20my%20latest%20trip%20cost%2C%20but%20it%20was%20in%20the%20millions.%20It's%20clear%20my%20five%20fellow%20passengers%20also%20had%20good%20financial%20outcomes%20in%20life.%20Richard%20Scott%20is%20a%20reproductive%20endocrinologist%20who%20sold%20his%20reproductive%20medicine%20group%2C%20IVIRMA%2C%20to%20private%20equity%20firm%20KKR.%20Elaine%20Chia%20Hyde%2C%20a%20physicist%2C%20pilot%2C%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20media%20company%20Chicago%20Star%20and%20the%20only%20woman%20on%20the%20trip%2C%20had%20been%20saving%20for%20years%20to%20do%20something%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spent%20about%20two%20and%20a%20half%20days%20in%20classroom%20training%20before%20takeoff.%20Unlike%20astronauts%20who%20prepare%20for%20longer%20orbital%20trips%2C%20we%20spent%20no%20time%20training%20in%20a%20centrifuge%20or%20swimming%20in%20a%20tank%20to%20understand%20weightlessness.%20This%20was%20more%20about%20learning%20the%20engineering%20behind%20the%20rocket%20so%20you%20know%20how%20safe%20it%20is.%20Up%20until%20two%20and%20a%20half%20minutes%20before%20they%20pull%20the%20gangplank%2C%20though%2C%20you%20can%20bail%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20takeoff%20we%20get%20into%20the%20designated%20crew%20capsule%20of%20the%20rocket.%20For%20the%20first%20five%20to%20seven%20seconds%2C%20you%20don't%20feel%20much%20movement%20because%20the%20engine%20is%20igniting.%20You%20have%20earpieces%20to%20soften%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20engine%2C%20but%20you%20still%20hear%20a%20lot%20of%20banging.%20Then%2C%20the%20capsule%20is%20ejected%20into%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20and%20a%20half%20minutes%2C%20you're%20crossing%20the%20K%C3%A1rm%C3%A1n%20line%2C%20and%20you%20start%20to%20realize%20how%20thin%20and%20fragile%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20is.%20By%20then%2C%20you're%20also%20weightless.%20I%20used%20my%20GoPro%20to%20get%20a%20shot%20of%20the%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ascent%20is%20smooth%2C%20but%20the%20descent%20can%20get%20bumpy.%20You're%20pulled%20into%20your%20seat%20with%20such%20a%20high%20gravitational%20acceleration%20that%20you%20can't%20physically%20move%20%E2%80%94%20let%20alone%20take%20a%20deep%20breath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20landed%2C%20our%20families%20were%20there%20to%20welcome%20us.%20We%20had%20a%20Champagne%20toast%20and%20took%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20were%20one%20of%20a%20few%20hundred%20civilians%20that%20had%20ventured%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae14ec18-ee7f-43a2-ba31-a28a1d85df28%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBillionaires%20for%20space%20travel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20interacted%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-life-career-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJeff%20Bezos%3C%2Fa%3E'%20company%20Amazon%20back%20in%20the%20nineties%20when%20I%20was%20a%20product%20manager%20launching%20AT%26amp%3BT's%20internet%20business%20and%20Amazon%20was%20launching%20book%20sales%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%8AI%20wouldn't%2