sident%20Donald%20Trump's%20policy%20decisions%2C%20which%20have%20angered%20some%20foreign%20visitors%20and%20prompted%20fear%20of%20a%20surge%20in%20prices%20and%20a%20stronger%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20traveler%20arrivals%20in%20the%20United%20States%20are%20expected%20to%20decline%20by%205.1%20percent%20in%202025%20compared%20to%20last%20year%2C%20against%20a%20previously%20projected%20increase%20of%208.8%20percent%2C%20Tourism%20Economics%20said%20in%20a%20report%20published%20late%20last%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20spending%20is%20expected%20to%20slide%2010.9%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20report's%20publication%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20situation%20has%20deteriorated%20further%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20outcome%20will%20likely%20be%20even%20worse%2C%20Tourism%20Economics%20president%20Adam%20Sacks%20said%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20effects%20of%20antipathy%20towards%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20slapped%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20China%20--%20and%20threatened%20to%20impose%20them%20on%20the%20European%20Union.%20A%20sweeping%20plan%20to%20curb%20immigration%20has%20intensified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20bodies%20like%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%20have%20been%20decimated%2C%20thousands%20of%20civil%20servants%20from%20lawyers%20to%20park%20rangers%20have%20been%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20Trump%20has%20drawn%20up%20controversial%20plans%20for%20the%20wars%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20situation%20with%20polarizing%20Trump%20Administration%20policies%20and%20rhetoric...%20will%20discourage%20travel%20to%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tourism%20Economics%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Oxford%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20organizations%20will%20feel%20pressure%20to%20avoid%20hosting%20events%20in%20the%20US%2C%20or%20sending%20employees%20to%20the%20US%2C%20cutting%20into%20business%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Tourism%20Forum%20Institute%20said%20a%20mix%20of%20stringent%20immigration%20policies%2C%20a%20strong%20dollar%20and%20global%20political%20tensions%20%26quot%3Bcould%20significantly%20affect%26quot%3B%20international%20arrivals%2C%20%26quot%3Bpotentially%20reshaping%20the%20nation's%20tourism%20sector%20for%20years%20to%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20residents%20of%2016%20European%20and%20Asian%20countries%20surveyed%20by%20YouGov%20in%20December%2C%2035%20percent%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20come%20to%20the%20United%20States%20under%20Trump%2C%20while%2022%20percent%20were%20more%20likely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20bit%20scared'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20tourists%20from%20France%2C%20Uzbekistan%2C%20and%20Argentina%20interviewed%20by%20AFP%20in%20New%20York's%20Times%20Square%2C%20Trump's%20stance%20has%20not%20upended%20their%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarianela%20Lopez%20and%20Ailen%20Hadjikovakis%2C%20both%2033%2C%20nevertheless%20used%20their%20European%20passports%20rather%20than%20their%20Argentine%20ones%20to%20avoid%20any%20problems%20at%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20a%20bit%20scared%20about%20the%20situation%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20change%20our%20plans%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lopez.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lagardere%20family%2C%20who%20came%20from%20France%2C%20said%20it%20hadn't%20impacted%20their%20plans%20either.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Americans%20%26quot%3Belected%20this%20president.%20It's%20democracy.%20If%20they're%20not%20happy%2C%20they'll%20change%20it%20in%20four%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Laurent%20Lagardere%2C%2054.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20is%20who%20he%20is%26quot%3B%20and%20avoiding%20the%20United%20States%20%26quot%3Bwon't%20change%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Lagardere%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%2077.7%20million%20foreign%20tourists%20were%20expected%20in%202024%2C%20up%2017%20percent%20year-on-year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Travel%20and%20Tourism%20Office%2C%20which%20does%20not%20yet%20have%20final%20figures%20for%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECanadians%20saying%20no%20to%20New%20York%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETourists%20from%20Western%20Europe%20--%20who%20made%20up%2037%20percent%20of%20visitors%20in%202024%20--%20are%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20choose%20other%20destinations%2C%20along%20with%20Canadians%20and%20Mexicans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Travel%20Association%20warned%20in%20early%20February%20that%20customs%20tariffs%20would%20deter%20Canadians%2C%20the%20largest%20contingent%20of%20foreign%20tourists%20in%20the%20United%20States%20with%2020.4%20million%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Statistics%20Canada%2C%20the%20number%20of%20Canadians%20returning%20from%20the%20United%20States%20fell%2023%20percent%20in%20February%20year-on-year%2C%20the%20second%20consecutive%20monthly%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20York%2C%20which%20welcomed%2012.9%20million%20foreign%20travelers%20in%202024%2C%20the%20effect%20is%20already%20noticeable%2C%20with%20Canadians%20canceling%20tour%20bookings%20and%20a%20drop%20in%20online%20searches%20for%20hotels%20or%20Broadway%20shows%2C%20NYC%20Tourism%20president%20Julie%20Coker%20told%20AFP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20lowered%20her%20forecast%20for%20the%20year%20in%20February%20but%20said%20that%20so%20far%2C%20only%20Canadians%20are%20saying%20no%20to%20Trump's%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20currently%20seeing%20anything%20from%20the%20UK%20or%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20it's%20too%20early%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20definitely%20watching%20that%20very%20closely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20British%20and%20German%20authorities%20have%20just%20warned%20their%20nationals%20to%20be%20extra%20v